Package: asciiwright
Type: Package
Title: ASCII Wright Maps in R
Version: 0.16.0
Author: Hao Zhou [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Hao Zhou <haozhou@szu.edu.cn>
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      given = "Hao",
      family = "Zhou",
      role = c("aut", "cre"),
      email = "haozhou@szu.edu.cn"
    )
  )
Description: Creates Winsteps-inspired Wright maps as fixed-width ASCII text.
    The package aligns person and item locations on a shared latent-variable
    axis and annotates means and standard deviations in a text layout that
    works well in terminals, reports, and plain-text outputs, including
    mirrored easiness tables, score columns, paginated console output, and
    polytomous threshold/range map variants.
